The project aims at facilitating the return of children to school in areas affected by Hurricane Matthew by rehabilitating and providing equipment to children, teachers and for food at school programs, while conducting disaster risk reduction at school and community level to increase the resilience of targeted areas. The project will rehabilitate 60 schools for a total amount of beneficiaries of 21000 in three departements : Nippes (26 schools), South (8 schools) and Grande Anse (26 schools).  (Nov 2016-May 2018 portion of multiyear award, 2016-2019 total EUR 1.7 million)
